 Scott Brown, Michael Dobstadt, Sean Eedy, Thomas Elsaesser, IanFleishman, Christina Gerhardt, Lisa Haegele, Randall Halle, Priscilla Layne, Ervin Malakaj, Kalani Michell, Evelyn Preuss, Patricia Anne Simpson, Fabian Tietke, Andrew Stefan Weiner. Christina Gerhardt is Associate Professor of German and Film Studies at the University of Hawai'i at Manoa. Marco Abel is Professor of English and Film Studies at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxHistoryy20th centuryzAustria. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryzGermany (East). 0aMotion picturesxHistoryzGermany (West). 4aFilm & Theatre. 4aGerman Literature. 4aModern History. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a1968.  aFrench cinéma vérité.  aGerman cinema.  aUS direct cinema.  acinema.  acultural and political happenings.  acultural impact.  arevolution.  ascreen cultures.1 aAbel, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbel, Marco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaumgärtel, Tilman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernstorff, Madeleine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Timothy Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobstadt, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEedy, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsaesser, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleishman, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhardt, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhardt, Christina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocab